<subSubSection id="90CA5FEDC7CC1D0AB2BA0B4FF1FA281B" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="5A27EB2F5C1186329FBFCE876588F683" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D5B480564487194374C0F6FB8EE7CF5F" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
The species is sufficiently described by 
<bibRefCitation id="3F6D0504C21F5C737D79B817C5FD6EAF" author="Verseveldt, J" journalOrPublisher="Amsterdam" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="69 - 171" title="Octocorallia from north-western Madagascar (Part IIIa-d)." volumeTitle="Proceedings Koninklijke Nederlandse Akademie van Wetenschappen" year="1973">Verseveldt (1973</bibRefCitation>
: 98). Here I show the drawing of the polyp as presented by 
<bibRefCitation id="E74DD2B6404E34A017D1D5F271D7F50D" author="Verseveldt, J" journalOrPublisher="Amsterdam" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="69 - 171" title="Octocorallia from north-western Madagascar (Part IIIa-d)." volumeTitle="Proceedings Koninklijke Nederlandse Akademie van Wetenschappen" year="1973">Verseveldt (1973</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 22a). The colony, which was not shown by Verseveldt (Figure 17), together with SEM images of the sclerites (Figures 18-19).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2115E0713F4431592E9A403BFAEB371E" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName id="F638F53A7E8829EE16E88A722650FA7A" class="Anthozoa" family="Nephtheidae" genus="Litophyton" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Litophyton bumastum" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="bumastum">Litophyton bumastum</taxonomicName>
is the only 
<taxonomicName id="95F1B0975D88DA575C7AD877EE252083" class="Anthozoa" family="Nephtheidae" genus="Litophyton" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Litophyton" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">Litophyton</taxonomicName>
species in the western Indian Ocean described with the adaxial side of the polyps lacking sclerites.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
